  "nursesNote": "ECT sends a brief electrical current to trigger a short seizure under anesthesia, used for severe or treatment-resistant depression. Before: verify informed consent, keep the patient NPO, have them void, and remove dentures/jewelry. After: place side-lying and check the airway, then expect temporary confusion, short-term memory loss, and headache. The nurse stays with the patient, reorients often, and supervises for fall risk.",
